2.caption: 1995 Major League Baseball All-Star Game
2.description: The 1995 Major League Baseball All-Star Game was the 66th playing of the midsummer classic between the all-stars of the American League (AL) and National League (NL), the two leagues comprising Major League Baseball. The game was held on July 11, 1995, at The Ballpark in Arlington in Arlington, Texas, the home of the Texas Rangers of the American League. It was the first All-Star Game held in the Dallas-Fort Worth area, but not the first hosted by the franchise (as the Washington Senators, the team hosted the game in 1962 and 1969).
2.inspected:Radio announcers: John Rooney, Jerry Coleman and Jeff Torborg
2.inspected:TV announcers: Al Michaels, Tim McCarver and Jim Palmer
